6:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Both Gate.io and Phemex use 8-hour funding cycles with rates calculated from mark-index spread and premium/discount mechanisms. Gate.io applies funding across 1,700+ perpetual contracts including micro-cap tokens, creating diverse arbitrage opportunities but with varying liquidity depths. Phemex focuses on major pairs with tighter spreads due to their derivatives specialization, though their smaller user base can create temporary rate inefficiencies. Gate.io's broader market coverage often shows higher volatility in funding rates for altcoin perpetuals."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lb",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which exchange has better funding rate arbitrage opportunities?","answer":"Gate.io offers more diverse opportunities with 1,700+ perpetual contracts, while Phemex provides better fee efficiency on major pairs with 0.01% maker fees versus Gate.io's 0.015%."},{"question":"How do funding rate calculations differ between Gate.io and Phemex?","answer":"Both use 8-hour cycles with mark price mechanisms, but Gate.io's broader token selection creates more volatile funding rates on altcoins, while Phemex's major-pair focus yields more stable rates."},{"question":"Which platform is better for large volume funding arbitrage?","answer":"Phemex's lower maker fees benefit high-volume strategies on major pairs, while Gate.io's deeper overall market provides better execution for diversified arbitrage across multiple altcoin perpetuals."},{"question":"Do both exchanges support cross-margin for funding arbitrage?","answer":"Yes, both support cross-margin trading which is essential for funding rate arbitrage strategies, with Phemex offering cleaner portfolio management tools and Gate.io providing broader collateral options."}]}]
